This paper deals with the Capacitated Vehicle Routing problem, which is a classic problem in operations research and computer science. The problem involves finding a set of tours that collectively cover all client demand, while respecting capacity constraints and minimizing the sum of tour lengths. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given the nature of the problem and the techniques used in the paper, it is likely that it would be classified under one or more of these sub-categories.
